<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Halflings also take care of their own</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:47 p.m. 18/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Halflings also take care of their own<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1534" TARGET=_self>Answer, please disregard above post.</A> (Ceyana)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>There was one instance of a Halfling PKing his own and he was driven from the community. We are beginning to form KOS lists, and race traitors certainly make the top of the list. Currently I only view evil races as enemies to my Halfling character, although my world views may change over time depending on what sort of welcome I receive in the other communities.
<P>&gt; I play a dark elf on the PvP server, and have since phase 4. I
<BR>&gt; somewhat feared that the server might become what you descibed,
<BR>&gt; but in reality it's nothing like that. As far as the dark elves
<BR>&gt; go, we police our own kind. I only heard of one or two players
<BR>&gt; pking other dark elves, and a warning was shouted about these
<BR>&gt; bad apples. I did see people pking other dark elves if one
<BR>&gt; looted a corpse that wasn't his/hers, but thats just called
<BR>&gt; policing (-: I would do the same thing.
<P>&gt; I don't know about the other races though, so I can only tell
<BR>&gt; you about the dark elves. Though the dark elves are the only
<BR>&gt; race that matters (-:
<P>&gt; - Ceyana
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
